        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:21PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Low Gap Shelter, or 10
miles southeast of Blairsville, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hiawassee, Young Harris, Blue Mountain Shelter, Brasstown Bald,
Titus, Mountain Scene, Woods Hole Shelter, Low Gap Shelter, Vogel
State Park, Track Rock, Tate City, Anna Ruby Falls, Macedonia, Plum
Orchard Gap Shelter, and Blood Mountain Shelter.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
